{"word":"αἰνός","slug":"αἰνός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰνός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:δεινός'><el>δεινός</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>dread, dire, grim</i>, terrible, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>αἰνότατε Κρονίδη</el> <i>most dread</i> son of Cronus, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-νῶς</el>, <i>terribly</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>strangely, exceedingly</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; also <el>αἰνά</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>-ότατον</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}